resources.string:

Generate a workout for these muscle groups:
%1$s
The total duration required for completing the workout would be:
%2$s
Additional workout requirements (optional):
%3$s

The response should only contain a JSON instance of the following data classes:

data class Workout(
    var title: String? = "",
    var description: String? = "",
    var duration: Long,
    var exerciseList: List<Exercise> = listOf(),
)

data class Exercise(
    var title: String? = "",
    var description: String? = "",
    var numberOfRepetitions: Int,
    var numberOfCircles: Int,
    var durationOfOneCircle: Long,
    var durationOfRest: Long,
    var exerciseType: ExerciseType,
)

enum class ExerciseType {
    TIME, REPETITION
}

Explanations for the fields in the classes:

Workout:
    title - workout title
    description - workout description
    duration - approximate duration of the workout

Exercise:
    title - exercise title
    description - exercise description
    numberOfRepetitions - number of repetitions per circle
    numberOfCircles - number of circles
    durationOfOneCircle - duration of one circle in milliseconds
    durationOfRest - rest duration between circles

An instance of the Exercise class can be of two types:
TIME - Exercises to be performed for a specific duration
REPETITIONS - Exercises to be performed for a specific number of repetitions

In the description, provide detailed instructions for performing each exercise

Time should be specified in milliseconds, and the duration of one circle for an exercise should not be less than 30 seconds
